\# Sticky Notes Application

A full-stack web application built with Django that allows users to create, view, edit, and delete personal notes. This project demonstrates core concepts of Django development, including the MVT (Model-View-Template) architecture, database models, and unit testing.

\---

\#\# Features

\- \*\*Full CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) functionality:\*\* Users can manage their notes through a simple web interface.  
\- \*\*Data Persistence:\*\* Notes are stored in a SQLite database, ensuring that data is saved between sessions.  
\- \*\*Unit Testing:\*\* The project includes a comprehensive suite of unit tests to ensure the correctness and reliability of the models, forms, and views.  
\- \*\*Modularity:\*\* The application is organized into separate modules (models, forms, views, URLs) to promote clean, maintainable code.

\#\# How to Get Started

Follow these steps to set up and run the project on your local machine:

1\.  \*\*Clone the repository:\*\*  
    \`\`\`bash  
    git clone https://github.com/G3rtPB87/G3rtPB87\_Dev.git  
    \`\`\`

2\.  \*\*Navigate to the project directory:\*\*  
    \`\`\`bash  
    cd sticky\_notes\_app  
    \`\`\`

3\.  \*\*Set up a virtual environment:\*\*  
    \`\`\`bash  
    python3 \-m venv venv  
    source venv/bin/activate  
    \`\`\`

4\.  \*\*Install dependencies:\*\*  
    \`\`\`bash  
    pip install \-r requirements.txt  
    \`\`\`

5\.  \*\*Run database migrations:\*\*  
    \`\`\`bash  
    python manage.py migrate  
    \`\`\`

6\.  \*\*Start the development server:\*\*  
    \`\`\`bash  
    python manage.py runserver  
    \`\`\`

7\.  Open your web browser and go to \`http://127.0.0.1:8000/\` to view the application.

\---

\#\# Unit Tests

The project includes unit tests to verify the core functionality. To run the tests, use the following command:

\`\`\`bash  
python manage.py test notes  
\`\`\`
